Odaily Planet Daily News French Hill, Chairman of the U.S. House Financial Services Committee, released a blueprint for U.S. digital assets, proposing six principles: 
1. Legislation must promote innovation; 
2. Legislation must clarify the classification of assets; 
3. Legislation must compile a framework for issuing new digital assets; 
4. Legislation must establish supervision of spot market exchanges and intermediaries; 
5. Legislation must establish best practices for protecting customer assets; 
6. Legislation must protect innovative decentralized projects and activities. (CoinDesk)
